Kubernetes YAML Cheat-Sheet (Mandatory Fields Only)
Resource	apiVersion	kind	metadata	spec / key fields	Notes
Pod	v1	Pod	name, namespace, labels	containers: list ‚Üí name, image, ports	Minimal pod: only containers & image required. Labels optional unless used in Service/Deployment.
Deployment	apps/v1	Deployment	name, namespace	replicas, selector.matchLabels, template ‚Üí metadata.labels, template ‚Üí spec ‚Üí containers	Selector must match template labels. Containers inside template.spec.
Service (ClusterIP)	v1	Service	name, namespace	type, selector (labels), ports: list ‚Üí port, targetPort	Selector matches Pod labels directly. ClusterIP default.
ConfigMap	v1	ConfigMap	name, namespace	data: key-value pairs	No spec. Keys are strings. Can be used in envFrom or mounted as files.
üß† Quick Reference Patterns
1Ô∏è‚É£ Pod Skeleton
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: <pod-name>
  namespace: default
  labels:
    app: <name>
spec:
  containers:
  - name: <container-name>
    image: <image>
    ports:
    - containerPort: <port>

2Ô∏è‚É£ Deployment Skeleton
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: <deployment-name>
  namespace: default
spec:
  replicas: <number>
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: <label>
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: <label>
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: <container-name>
        image: <image>
        ports:
        - containerPort: <port>

3Ô∏è‚É£ Service Skeleton
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: <service-name>
  namespace: default
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  selector:
    app: <label>
  ports:
  - port: <service-port>
    targetPort: <container-port>

4Ô∏è‚É£ ConfigMap Skeleton
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: <configmap-name>
  namespace: default
data:
  KEY1: value1
  KEY2: value2

5Ô∏è‚É£ Using ConfigMap in Deployment
containers:
- name: <container-name>
  image: <image>
  envFrom:
  - configMapRef:
      name: <configmap-name>

‚úÖ How to Use This Cheat-Sheet

Pick your resource (Pod, Deployment, Service, ConfigMap).

Fill the placeholders (<name>, <label>, <image>).

Check labels & selectors ‚Äî they must match for Deployment ‚Üí Pods and Service ‚Üí Pods.

Add optional features later: env vars, volumes, probes, resources.
